      <sentence>
        <infon key="n">8</infon>
        <offset>1161</offset>
        <text>Our results suggest that changes in the SAM, including recent and projected trends attributed to human activity, drive variations in Southern Ocean mixed-layer depth, with consequences for air-sea exchange, ocean sequestration of heat and carbon, and biological productivity.
</text>
